    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Unhealthy Food Habits</h2>
        <p>Unhealthy food habits are choices that negatively impact your physical and mental well-being. Examples include overeating processed foods, high sugar consumption, and lack of balanced meals. These habits can lead to obesity, heart disease, and other chronic conditions.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="impact">
        <h2>Impact on Health</h2>
        <p>Consuming unhealthy foods regularly can result in:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Weight gain and obesity</li>
            <li>Increased risk of heart disease</li>
            <li>Digestive issues</li>
            <li>Decreased energy levels</li>
            <li>Weakened immune system</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="tips">
        <h2>Healthy Eating Tips</h2>
        <p>Follow these tips to improve your diet:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Eat more whole foods like fruits and vegetables.</li>
            <li>Limit processed and sugary foods.</li>
            <li>Stay hydrated with water.</li>
            <li>Practice portion control.</li>
            <li>Make time for regular physical activity.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

